[1]
Date: Thu 10 Feb 2011
Source: Yonhap News Agency [edited]
<http://english.yonhapnews.co.kr/northkorea/2011/02/10/91/0401000000AEN20110210000700320F.HTML>


Foot-and-mouth disease breaks out in North Korea
------------------------------------------------
North Korea has reported to the Food and Agriculture Organization of
the United Nations [FAO] an outbreak of the livestock foot-and-mouth
(FMD) disease on its soil, the Radio Free Asia said in a report on
Thursday [10 Feb 2011].

North Korea's agricultural ministry sent a letter to the UN
organization on Wednesday [9 Feb 2011], notifying it of the outbreak
of the contagious animal disease and asking for emergency support, the
media reported, citing a UN official.

The official did not mention the region of the outbreak nor the
number of livestock that showed FMD symptoms, it added. [Other
not-reported data are the animal species affected, the mode of
diagnosis, the vaccination status of the affected animals, and the
identity of the FMDV serotype involved. - Mod.AS]

The organization will send experts to North Korea "at an appropriate
time" to help the reclusive communist country contain the FMD disease,
it said.

--
